  "title": "Can't change price field",
  "body": "Is there any way to change \"price\" filed in price widgets?\r\n\r\nI want to do it like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nvar countryPrice = \"price\" //default value\r\nif(any logic){\r\n  countryPrice = \"price_gb\"\r\n}\r\n-------\r\nsearch.addWidget(instantsearch.widgets.rangeSlider({\r\n    container: '#price',\r\n    attributeName: countryPrice,\r\n    (...)\r\n}))\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut it doesn't work. I've got that error: \r\n```\r\ngenerate-ranges.js:11 Uncaught TypeError: Cannot read property 'min' of undefined\r\n    at i (generate-ranges.js:11)\r\n    at Object._generateRanges (connectPriceRanges.js:118)\r\n    at Object.render (connectPriceRanges.js:183)\r\n    at InstantSearch.js:317\r\n    at n (_arrayEach.js:15)\r\n    at r (forEach.js:37)\r\n    at t.value (InstantSearch.js:313)\r\n    at r.n.emit (events.js:84)\r\n    at algoliasearch.helper.js:1245\r\n    at n (_arrayEach.js:15)\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhat I am missing? ",
